\pard\plain \li360\sa120 \f20 rtftohtml was generating "unknown symbol" errors for optional destinations (RTF with a markup of \{\\*\\xxx ... \}
 The convention for RTF readers is that any optional destination that a reader does not understand should be silently ignored. This bug was also causing extra text to be inserted into HTML files.\par 
